@node About "About On-Time."

	@{u}About On-Time.@{uu}

On-Time is a personal schedule database/organiser. It allows you to keep track of everyday events in an easily understandable manner. If it is used in conjunction with the program @{"Alarmist©" link RunningAlarmist} (by the same author) it can be used to remind you of future events.

On-Time takes a slightly different and simplified approach to keeping track of events. Some programs provide a diary like interface where you see pages with each days events on them. Instead, On-Time uses  simple lists to display events in chronological order. Along with this it uses a standard calendar that is linked to the Event lists to show events at a glance.

Make sure you take the time to read the entire On-Time documentation as there are little things here and there that make life easier.

On-Time is a MUI(Magic User Interface) application. This means you need the MUI files/library to use On-Time. Version 3.3 of MUI is required. I chose to develop using MUI because of its flexibility and easy of use, both for the user and programmer. MUI is hopefully the direction of the future. MUI is available as a reduced product on the Public Domain, but if you wish to have full control, and support a great product that supports the continuing life of the Amiga, then @{"register" link MUI_Register} for the full version.

OnTime© is classified FreeWare. See @{"Disclaimer" link Disclaimer}.

Mathew Wilson

