	@{u}Maybe In the Future...@{uu}

- I would firstly like to sincerely apologize for the fact that this program is not @{u}fully@{uu} object oriented in design. There are about 9 different classes operating within OnTime at the moment but the back bone of the program is still not split up into classes.  I am relatively new to C programming (April '94) and I don't know any local experienced programmers to confer with (have no direct Internet access either!) With no technical manuals and very little documentation, I am in this alone. I am currently trying to teach myself many things, one being OO program design. Hopefully in the near future this program will be fully OO in design. If I stay with the Amiga then I will be committed to eventually produce OO designed programs. So please be patient and hold back the abuse for now 8). Hopefully I'll stay with Amiga.

